<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="83" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,1772,1941]" pageId="18" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1772,1797]" pageId="18" pageNumber="83">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male of the new species is similar to that of the south-westpalaearctic 
<taxonomicName authority="Perez" authorityName="Perez" box="[1128,1358,1772,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinguiculus">
<emphasis box="[1128,1288,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="83">S. pinguiculus</emphasis>
Pérez
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Bluthgen" authorityName="Bluthgen" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="83">S. intermedius</emphasis>
Blüthgen
</taxonomicName>
by the face with apressed white pubescence below as well as above the antennal sockets and the metasomal terga (including T 
<number box="[540,550,1845,1869]" pageId="18" pageNumber="83" value="1.0">1</number>
) densely punctate (
<taxonomicName box="[780,943,1844,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinguiculus">
<emphasis box="[780,943,1844,1869]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="83">S. pinguiculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group). It differs from this species by the short, triangular gonostylus (
<figureCitation box="[478,609,1880,1905]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 61" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1342,1364]" captionTargetBox="[210,1373,198,1309]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[200,1387,193,1320]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 61. Males, gonostylus, dorsal and lateral views: 46, 47 — Sphecodes nippon; 48, 49 — S. pinguiculus Pérez; 50, 51 — S. puncticeps Thomson; 52, 53 — S. reticulatus Thomson; 54, 55 — S. rufiventris (Panzer); 56, 57 — S. scabricollis Wesmael; 58, 59 — S. schwarzi, sp. nov.; 60, 61 — S. spinulosus Hagens. Dark indicate thickened areas. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/234177/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="83">
Figs 
<number box="[536,609,1880,1905]" pageId="18" pageNumber="83" value="58.59">58, 59</number>
</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName box="[665,826,1880,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinguiculus">
<emphasis box="[665,826,1880,1905]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="83">S. pinguiculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[883,1045,1880,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[883,1045,1880,1905]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="83">S. intermedius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the gonostylus is long and almost rectangular).
</paragraph>
